supportsBackrefTracking

public boolean supportsBackrefTracking()
Description copied from class: DmcObject
If a class of object doesn't support back reference tracking, it will overload this method to return false. Otherwise, back reference tracking can be turned on for all objects. This distinction is important for things like Dark Matter Protocol messages where we would want to ensure that object references could be resolved, but we wouldn't want to update back references in those objects to which the messages referred.

Overrides:
supportsBackrefTracking in class DmcObject
Returns:
true if the object supports backref tracking.
